Reasoning: The paper deals with the capacity and achievable rates of Gaussian relay channels, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The consideration of noise correlation also suggests a possible fit in the Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category. The use of different relay schemes (DF, CF, AF) and power allocation strategies may also relate to the Communications (cs.COMM) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
